She cofounded Off the Mat, Into the World which has raised more than four million dollars for communities in need.'] Average Rating: 4.7 Product Details: {'Genre': 'Exercise & Fitness', 'Format': 'Multiple Formats, Box set, Color, NTSC', 'Contributor': 'YOGA OF AWAKENING: CHAKRA FLOW', 'Language': 'English', 'Number Of Discs': '3', 'Aspect Ratio': '1.33:1', 'MPAA rating': 'Unrated (Not Rated)', 'Product Dimensions': '0.7 x 7.5 x 5.4 inches; 2.72 Ounces', 'Item model number': 'unknown', 'Media Format': 'Multiple Formats, Box set, Color, NTSC', 'Run time': '4 hours', 'Release date': 'January 27, 2015', 'Studio': 'Sounds True', 'Number of discs': '3'} Review Text: I bought this because I wanted to get into doing yoga but didn't have time or a baby sitter to actually go out to a studio and do it. I wanted to do it for a form of exercise and get some flexibility as well.

I came across this DVD here on Amazon, which had good reviews and seemed like what i was looking for.

I have had it for about 2 years now and i love it and im very happy i got it! it has individual sessions for each chakra, or one long one for all! If I have a lot of time I like to do the long one.

My fiance also loves it too and he started doing it everyday. He was having back tightness and pain and i told him to try my yoga DVD, and the stretching ended up helping to alleviate the pain!

In some of the reviews on her DVDs, I noticed people complaining about her talking through it, but I absolutely love what she says, it is very inspirational and I feel like it helps me even more get into a relaxed and loving state!

I would not buy any other yoga DVD by anyone else! Review Title: A great exercise and spiritual practice all in one! However, the individual demonstrates a significant variation in sentiment, as seen from extreme reactions such as loving certain films while finding others intolerable.

The person seeks both excitement in storytelling and a means for personal development or fitness. Quality emerges as a recurring theme, with specific mention of favorable experiences leading to high satisfaction ratings. Despite this, there are signs of price sensitivity and cautious selection, as seen in thorough evaluations before purchases. 

Overall, this individual values engaging and quality-driven media that aligns with family values and holistic wellness practices, while also seeking convenience and affordability in their entertainment and fitness pursuits.

target_interaction.title: Boring - Not good at keeping your attention
target_interaction.text: My 6 year old picked this to watch; we are both big fans of alice in wonderland movies. Something about it could not grab/keep my attention. Just overall hard to follow and boring. Glad we did not actually have to pay to rent this. Also in this movie Alice is suppose to be 7 1/2, she looks my age (in her 20s) LOL. Weird.
description: In this modern adaptation of the classic children's story "Alice Through the Looking Glass," written by Lewis Carroll, Alice (Kate Beckinsale) returns to Wonderland. There, she meets the Red and White Queens, as well as many other amusing friends on her journey across the chessboard countryside to become a crowned queen. Steve Coogan, Ian Holm and Penelope Wilton also star.
